HEADWORD: Essorant
<hw>Es"so*rant</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F.]</ety>
<fld>(Her.)</fld> <def>Standing, but with the wings spread, as if about
to fly; -- said of a bird borne as a charge on an escutcheon.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

